 Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a nickname for a blonde, from <i>blanche</i>, feminine of Old French <i>blanc</i> ‘white’ (of Germanic origin). It came to be associated with the notion of whiteness as indicating purity, and was introduced into England as a given name by the Normans. A pale complexion combined with light hair was long an ideal of beauty in Europe (compare Modern English <i>fair</i>, which at first meant ‘beautiful’ and then, from the 16th century, ‘light in colouring’)."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Blanche de Breteuil Dame de Breteuil was born in 1091, in Breteuil-sur-Iton, Eure, Upper Normandy, France, her father, Waléran de Breteuil II,  Seig de Breteuil e de Creil, was 26 and her mother, Judith Ivette De Saint-Just En Chaussée, was 17. She had at least 2 sons with Gérard II dit Le Preux DE HAM-DE WALCOURT. She died in 1146, in Ham, Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 55."},"et":{"1091–1146":"1091–1146","1095–1147":"1095–1147","1096–1115":"1096–1115","1080–1132":"1080–1132","1115–1182":"1115–1182","–Male":"Surnud","1065–1124":"1065–1124","1074–1128":"1074–1128","1091":"1091","1080":"1080","1132":"1132","1065":"1065","1074":"1074","1096":"1096","1095":"1095","1182":"1182","1128":"1128","1115":"1115","1147":"1147","1124":"1124","1146":"1146","Breteuil, Oise, Picardie, França":"Breteuil, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Ham, Somme, Picardie, França":"Ham, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Tripoli, Ţarābulus, Libya":"Tripoli, Ţarābulus, Liibüa","Breteuil-sur-Iton, Eure, Haute-Normandie, França":"Breteuil-sur-Iton, Eure, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1091–1146":"1091–1146","1095–1147":"1095–1147","1096–1115":"1096–1115","1080–1132":"1080–1132","1115–1182":"1115–1182","–Male":"Kuollut","1065–1124":"1065–1124","1074–1128":"1074–1128","1091":"1091","1080":"1080","1132":"1132","1065":"1065","1074":"1074","1096":"1096","1095":"1095","1182":"1182","1128":"1128","1115":"1115","1147":"1147","1124":"1124","1146":"1146","Br